<subSubSection lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="418" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1625,2010]" lastBlockId="17.[151,1437,151,464]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="418" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1769,1794]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Length of forewing is 
<quantity box="[576,654,1770,1794]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
in males (Bayarsaykhan 
<emphasis box="[935,991,1769,1794]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">et al.</emphasis>
2017) and 
<quantity box="[1116,1257,1769,1794]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.275" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.25" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" unit="mm" value="12.75" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="12.5">12.5–13 mm</quantity>
in females. The species is similar externally to the sympatric 
<taxonomicName box="[680,843,1805,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Chionaema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klapperichi">
<emphasis box="[680,843,1805,1830]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">N. klapperichi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Bayarsaikhan &amp; Bae" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[905,1075,1805,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angkorensis">
<emphasis box="[905,1075,1805,1830]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">N. angkorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in the darker male hindwings and the narrower transverse lines of the forewing. The male genitalia differ clearly from both the externally similar species and are most similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2018" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" box="[822,988,1877,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomaswitti" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[822,988,1877,1902]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">N. thomaswitti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[996,1088,1877,1902]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[996,1088,1877,1902]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2018" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" box="[1146,1283,1877,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hortensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1146,1283,1877,1902]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">N. hortensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1292,1384,1877,1902]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1292,1384,1877,1902]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but differ from 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2018" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" box="[281,444,1913,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomaswitti" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[281,444,1913,1938]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">N. thomaswitti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[451,541,1913,1938]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[451,541,1913,1938]" pageId="16" pageNumber="417">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the significantly smaller apical lobes of the juxta, the narrower apical lobe of the costa, the narrower ventral costal plate with the much smaller ampulla, the absence of a weak basal dentation of the costa, the significantly longer and basally narrower subapical saccular process, the much larger thorn on the aedeagus carinal plate, and the more weak spines on the medial and distal diverticula of the vesica; from 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2018" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hortensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">N. hortensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[266,360,188,213]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[266,360,188,213]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
they differ in the smaller apical costal lobe, the slightly smaller ampulla, the much larger subapical saccular process, the much larger thorn on the aedeagus carinal plate, and the larger spines on the medial and distal diverticula of the vesica. The female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bae &amp; Bayarsaikhan" authorityYear="2017" box="[819,950,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Kailasha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="babensis">
<emphasis box="[819,950,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">N. babensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are most similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Volynkin &amp; Černý, 2018" authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Černý" authorityYear="2018" box="[1272,1436,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Nephelomilta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomaswitti" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1272,1436,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">N. thomaswitti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,243,295,320]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,243,295,320]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and differ in the slightly more elongated antevaginal plate, the more strongly sclerotized margin of the ostium bursae, the broader and more heavily sclerotized duscus bursae, the larger appendix bursae, the smaller spinules of the medial cluster of the corpus bursae, and the significantly smaller signum.
</paragraph>
